# Custom Diagram Canvas (P2 #7)

**Priority:** P2 (Medium)
**Estimated Time:** 25-35 hours
**Status:** Planning
**Created:** 2025-11-26
**Philosophy:** Build custom, no external diagram libraries - full control and privacy

---

## Overview

Build a **custom canvas-based diagram editor from scratch** using HTML5 Canvas API and SVG. This provides complete control, privacy, security, and the ability to integrate features from multiple competitors (Excalidraw, Apple Freeform, Draw.io, Microsoft Visio, Miro) into a unified Neuman Brain experience.

## Philosophy & Principles

**Why Build Custom:**
1. **Privacy & Security** - No external libraries means no external data leakage
2. **Full Control** - Can add any feature from any competitor
3. **Integration** - Deep integration with notes, tasks, custom fields
4. **Performance** - Optimized for our exact needs, no bloat
5. **IP Ownership** - 100% our technology
6. **Extensibility** - Foundation for future AI features (P4)
7. **Aligns with CLAUDE.md** - Build the best custom platform we can

**Competitors We'll Cherry-Pick From:**
- **Excalidraw** - Hand-drawn aesthetic, shapes library
- **Apple Freeform** - Infinite canvas, sticky notes, free-form layout
- **Draw.io/Visio** - Professional diagrams, connector routing, shape libraries
- **Miro** - Collaboration patterns, templates, frames
- **Figma** - Vector editing, precise controls, components

---

## Problem Statement

Users currently have:
- **No diagramming capability** - Can't create visual diagrams
- **External tool dependency** - Must use separate apps
- **No integration** - Diagrams disconnected from notes/tasks
- **Privacy concerns** - External tools collect data

**Use Cases:**
- **Developers:** Architecture diagrams, flowcharts, system design, ERDs
- **Project Managers:** Process flows, org charts, Gantt charts, mind maps
- **Students:** Concept maps, study diagrams, visual notes
- **Designers:** Wireframes, user flows, sitemaps, mockups
- **General:** Brainstorming, planning, visual thinking

