## Technical Architecture

### Canvas Rendering Strategy

**Hybrid Approach: SVG + Canvas**

**SVG for Shapes (Primary):**
- Easier to edit (move, resize, click detection)
- Native events (mousedown, click)
- Accessibility (can add ARIA labels)
- Export to SVG trivial
- Scales perfectly (vector)

**Canvas for Drawing Tools:**
- Freehand pen (smooth curves via perfect-freehand algorithm)
- Performance for complex paths
- Custom rendering effects

**Why Not Pure Canvas:**
- Hit detection is manual (harder)
- No native events (must track mouse state)
- Accessibility harder
- Export requires manual serialization

**Why Not Pure SVG:**
- Performance degrades with 1000+ elements
- Drawing tools less smooth

### Data Model

**Diagram:**
```typescript
interface Diagram {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  thumbnail?: string; // base64 PNG

  // Canvas state
  canvasState: CanvasState;

  // Elements
  elements: DiagramElement[];

  // Metadata
  tags?: string[];
  linkedNotes?: string[];
  linkedTasks?: string[];
}

interface CanvasState {
  zoom: number; // 1.0 = 100%
  pan: { x: number; y: number }; // viewport offset
  gridSize: number; // 20px default
  snapToGrid: boolean;
}

interface DiagramElement {
  id: string;
  type: 'rectangle' | 'circle' | 'ellipse' | 'triangle' | 'diamond' | 'line' | 'arrow' | 'text' | 'freehand' | 'connector';

  // Position & size
  x: number;
  y: number;
  width: number;
  height: number;
  rotation?: number; // degrees

  // Styling
  fill?: string; // hex color or 'transparent'
  stroke?: string;
  strokeWidth?: number;
  strokeStyle?: 'solid' | 'dashed' | 'dotted';
  cornerRadius?: number; // for rectangles

  // Text-specific
  text?: string;
  fontSize?: number;
  fontFamily?: string;
  fontWeight?: 'normal' | 'bold';
  textAlign?: 'left' | 'center' | 'right';

  // Connector-specific
  startPoint?: { x: number; y: number };
  endPoint?: { x: number; y: number };
  startArrow?: boolean;
  endArrow?: boolean;
  connectorType?: 'straight' | 'curved' | 'orthogonal';

  // Path-specific (freehand)
  points?: Array<{ x: number; y: number }>;

  // Z-index
  zIndex: number;
}
```

